<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="352" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,464,1421,1449]" box="[151,464,1421,1449]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,464,1421,1449]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,464,1421,1449]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352">
Genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Navas, 1928" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1928" box="[238,464,1421,1449]" class="Insecta" family="Mantispidae" genus="Plega" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,306,1422,1449]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="352">Plega</emphasis>
Navás, 1928
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1489,1803]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352">
Species of this genus are characterized by a mottled coloration pattern, a row of tubercles in the mid-line on distal half of fore femur that splits into two rows near the basal half (
<figureCitation box="[865,949,1525,1552]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1981,2006]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,200,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[201,1386,200,1938]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, head and prothorax, lateral; b, forelegs; c, male terminalia, lateral; d, same, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235148/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="352">Fig. 2b</figureCitation>
); laterally to the tubercles there is a row of stout setae restricted to the distal half of the femur (
<figureCitation box="[738,820,1561,1588]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1981,2006]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,200,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[201,1386,200,1938]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, head and prothorax, lateral; b, forelegs; c, male terminalia, lateral; d, same, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235148/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="352">Fig. 2b</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Parker, F. D. &amp; Stange, L. A." box="[844,1100,1560,1587]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" pagination="604 - 612" refId="ref11428" refString="Parker, F. D. &amp; Stange, L. A. (1965) Systematic and biological notes on the tribe Platymantispini (Neuroptera: Mantispidae) and the description of a new species of Plega from Mexico. Canadian Entomologist, 97, 604 - 612. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / Ent 97604 - 6" type="journal article" year="1965">Parker &amp; Stange 1965</bibRefCitation>
); the sub-basal major spine is present (
<figureCitation box="[248,333,1597,1624]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1981,2006]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,200,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[201,1386,200,1938]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, head and prothorax, lateral; b, forelegs; c, male terminalia, lateral; d, same, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235148/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="352">Fig. 2b</figureCitation>
); the foretrochanter lacks a medial dentiform process on inner surface (
<figureCitation box="[1140,1224,1597,1624]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1981,2006]" captionTargetBox="[201,1386,200,1938]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[201,1386,200,1938]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, head and prothorax, lateral; b, forelegs; c, male terminalia, lateral; d, same, ventral." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235148/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="352">Fig. 2b</figureCitation>
), and the forewing has the 
<emphasis box="[237,300,1633,1659]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="352">rarp2</emphasis>
cell curved (
<figureCitation box="[446,526,1633,1660]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1980,2005]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,185,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,185,1954]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Plega mixteca sp. n.: a, habitus of male holotype, lateral; b, wing venation." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3235146/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="352">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Penny, N. D." box="[551,703,1633,1659]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" pagination="209 - 223" refId="ref11533" refString="Penny, N. D. (1982 b) Review of the generic level classification of the New World Mantispidae (Neuroptera). Acta Amazonica, 12, 209 - 223. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 1809 - 43921982121209" type="journal article" year="1982">Penny 1982b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ardila-Camacho, A. &amp; Calle Tobon, A. &amp; Wolff, M. &amp; Stange, L. A." box="[713,1030,1633,1659]" pageId="1" pageNumber="352" pagination="295 - 324" refId="ref10384" refString="Ardila-Camacho, A., Calle Tobon, A., Wolff, M. &amp; Stange, L. A. (2018) New species and new distributional records of Neotropical Mantispidae (Insecta: Neuroptera). Zootaxa, 4413 (2), 295 - 324. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4413.2.4" type="journal article" year="2018">
Ardila-Camacho 
<emphasis box="[906,955,1633,1659]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="352">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
